[1]
Date: Mon 16 Aug 2021
Source: KABC [edited]
https://www.kabc.com/2021/08/16/rare-dog-disease-on-rise-in-west-la-county/


A rare disease found in dogs is making its way around west Los Angeles County. Leptospirosis is a bacterial disease, causing kidney failure and sometimes death. Animal health experts say they have seen an alarming increase of cases, calling it an "epidemic." Most cases are from the San Fernando Valley. There have been no reports of a death of a dog from the disease, but officials urge people to get their pets vaccinated as soon as possible.

